SeriesDescription: Implementation of standard accounting tools to monitor the economic and environmental aspects of tourism (number of tables)
Source:
Departamento Administrativo Nacional de Estadística (DANE) 
Tourism Satellite Account: Survey of Internal Tourism Expenditure - EGIT Survey of International Travelers - EVI Flow of internal travelers and outbound: Migration Colombia Great Integrated Survey of Households - GEIH 2015-2019 Matrix Input Product - MIP 2015 Annual accounts of goods and services-SEEA physical flow accounts for solid waste: 
Administrative record of final disposal of waste - Superintendency of Household Public Services Administrative record of solid waste use - Superintendency of Household Public Services Administrative record of subscribers of the public cleaning service - Superintendency of Household Public Services Administrative record of hazardous waste generation (RESPEL ) - IDEAM Annual sugarcane production - ASOCAÑA Industrial Environmental Survey (EAI) - DANE Annual Manufacturing Survey (EAM) - DANE Tables offer use of the National Accounts System - DANE Foreign trade statistics - DANE -SEEA physical flow accounts for air emissions:
Use of energy products within economic activities and households - Environmental and Economic Account of energy flows (DANE)
SEEA physical flow accounts for water: Industrial Environmental Survey (EAI) - DANE Tables offer use of the System of National Accounts - DANE National Population and Housing Census 2018 and Population Projections - DANE Area sown and harvested by crop - Ministry of Agriculture and Development Rural (MADR), guilds and DANE Inventories of cattle, poultry, pigs and aquaculture production - GIT annual accounts of goods and services of the DSCN of DANE Added value and by economic activity - Annual accounts of goods and services of DANE Generation of energy by hydroelectric plants - XM Compañía de Expertos en Mercados SA Information on volumes of water collected,distributed and used during the production and treatment process - Main aqueducts in the country number of subscribers and consumption billed in cubic meters (m3) and average water rates - Superintendence of Residential Public Services
SEEA physical flow accounts for energy:
Extraction, production of oil and extracted natural gas, losses - National Hydrocarbons Agency (ANH) Coal production - National Mining Agency (ANM) Demand for distributed natural gas - Concentrate Production of sugarcane bagasse, fuel alcohol - Sugar Balance , Association of Sugarcane Growers of Colombia (ASOCAÑA) Demand, production of coal, natural gas, oil - National Accounts, Environmental and Economic Account of Assets of Mining and Energy Resources (CAE-ARME), DANE Extraction and production of firewood - National Accounts, Economic and Environmental Account of forest flows, DANE Annual Manufacturing Survey (EAM), DANE Imports, exports, enclave and smuggling of oil, coal, natural gas,Petroleum derivatives - Foreign Trade Statistics and Supply Utilization Balances (BOU), DANE National Accounts Marine Diesel Imports - Quarterly Sample of Foreign Trade in Services, DANE Biofuel production - National Federation of Biofuels of Colombia (Fedebiocombistibles) Production and imports of gas liquefied petroleum and diesel oil (ACPM) - Mining-Energy Planning Unit (UPME) Production of electrical energy, generation of energy from renewable sources, intermediate consumption, losses - XM Compañía de Expertos en Mercados SADANE Biofuel production - National Federation of Biofuels of Colombia (Fedebiocombistibles) Production and imports of liquefied petroleum gas and diesel oil (ACPM) - Mining-Energy Planning Unit (UPME) Production of electricity, generation of energy from renewable sources, consumption intermediate, losses - XM Compañía de Expertos en Mercados SADANE Biofuel production - National Federation of Biofuels of Colombia (Fedebiocombistibles) Production and imports of liquefied petroleum gas and diesel oil (ACPM) - Mining-Energy Planning Unit (UPME) Production of electricity, generation of energy from renewable sources, consumption intermediate, losses - XM Compañía de Expertos en Mercados SA
FootNote: The Table 7 on employment in tourism industries was replaced by a separate annex that contains direct employment in the tourism sector for both the level of employed and Full-Time Equivalent Jobs based on a methodology derived from the input-output model
